THE GAME
--------

  'JackTrap' is a Workbench game where you have to get the jack
out of the 'trap'. The jack is located at the fourth position
under a series of 10 cards which are all face down. An empty
square as well as a pack containing the 41 remaining cards, all
face down, are located at the bottom of the game board.

  When you click on the card that is located above the jack, that
card will be turned over and then be removed from the game board.
If the colour shown on that card is red (heart or diamond), the
jack will move one position to the left. While a black colour
(spade or club) will move the jack toward the right. The removed
card will be replaced by a card from the pack at the bottom of the
game board.

  The game is won when the jack is moved from one end of the game
board (either at left or right), to the empty square located
below, before the pack of cards gets empty.

  Have fun!

